dataqual.logic: The following topological rules have been established and validated for these data: all features should be single part; no feature should self-intersect or self-overlap; points should be covered by the endpoint of a line; lines should be connected to points or another line, such that there should be no dangles or pseudonodes; and polygons should not overlap each other. Violations of these rules have been identified and fixed wherever possible. Where enough information is not available to fix them, the errors still exist. However, as more information becomes available to correct them, the errors will be fixed.
dataqual.complete: The primary focus of these data is electric transmission infrastructure, therefore there is minimal, if any, distribution infrastructure included. These data are by nature dynamic, as new infrastucture is built and others dismantled. Every effort is made to present the most current view of the changing industry landscape, however omissions will inevitably occur.

attracc.attraccr: These data have been compiled over a period of years from a variety of source materials, including paper maps, digital maps, digital data files and phone contact with asset owners/operators. All attribute information is verified with the asset owner or from at least two public sources by the Research staff.

horizpa.horizpar: These data have been assembled over a period of years from a variety of source materials with a variety of scales, including paper maps, digital maps, digital data files and phone contact with asset owners/operators. While all new data are placed with reference to high resolution imagery, this has not always been possible. Therefore, there is no comprehensive statement about source scale and the resulting spatial accuracy that can be made. However, there are feature-level attributes in the data that provide information about the scale or pixel resolution of the source used for placement. Users can review these fields to get an idea of the spatial accuracy of a particular feature.
